## #interrupt-cells

**Value type:** `<u32>`

The *#interrupt-cells* property defines the number of cells required to encode an interrupt specifier for an interrupt domain. This property is required on interrupt controller nodes and interrupt nexus nodes.

For example, an Open PIC interrupt controller uses 2 cells (interrupt number + level/sense); an ARM GIC uses 3 cells (type + number + flags).

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8550.dtsi — ARM GIC v3: 3 cells */
gic: interrupt-controller@17100000 {
    compatible = "arm,gic-v3";
    #interrupt-cells = <3>;
};

/* Open PIC: 2 cells */
open_pic: interrupt-controller@13370000 {
    interrupt-controller;
    #address-cells = <0>;
    #interrupt-cells = <2>;
};
```
